  "texts": [
    "The initial input to transformer models is the word embeddings of the text.",
    "These embeddings are then processed through multiple self-attention mechanisms and feed-forward networks present in the transformer architecture [1].",
    "As the information flows through the layers of a transformer, the model refines these embeddings, capturing contextual information from surrounding words.",
    "This ability to understand context is a significant advancement over traditional word embeddings, which are static and lack contextual awareness.The application of word vectors in transformer models, such as BERT, has led to breakthroughs in various NLP tasks [3].",
    "For instance, models like BERT utilize these embeddings to understand the context around a word, enabling superior performance in tasks like question answering, sentiment analysis, and more."
  ],
